snippet.textDisplay: I did something similar but more of a chiller design with a flooded barrel instead of an evaporator coil. Constant short cycling due to barely any load will kill a compressor.

snippet.textDisplay:
2:05 - sometimes welding is "throwing a bunch of chemicals at things" ;-) You should check out explosive welding... https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u9_bqafUJfA Sometimes you just 'throw' the metal together - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=42MUVQNPrXE - that process, in much smaller form is found in many car engines, many valves are made like that so the best materials are used for the purpose (and cost).

4:30, that's even better than what I was taught - to put a twist, or bend, on one end, so you don't accidentally poke a sharp end into your eye, or pick up the hot end in your bare fingers.
